                                        <h3 class="heavy-font">
                                        Introducing iARF, an injectable Autologous Regenerative Fibrin that restores facial volume and reduces signs of aging</h3>

                            </div>


                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">
                            <span class="main-color"><b>iARF</b></span> - Injectable Autologous Regenerative Fibrin contains ProtSmart 6 and 4x IDRIA G with blood draw components.</p> 
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">
                            The aqueous part of PRP is plasma, which is an acellular component containing proteins that are important for tissue regeneration. These proteins are involved in the tissue healing process and enable anti-inflammatory effects, clot stabilization, anti-microbial actions, cell-matrix adhesion, and tissue synthesis.</p>
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">One of the most important plasma cytokines is a2M. The alpha-2-macroglobulin molecule is synthesized mainly in the liver. But also locally by macrophages, fibroblasts, and it is the largest major non-immunoglobulin protein in the plasma. The alpha-2-macroglobulin acts as an antiprotease and can inactivate an enormous variety of proteinases.</p>

                            <div class="panel-body fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">
                            <table>
                                <tbody><tr>
                                    <td class="width-40 "><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                    <td>α2M is known as a ubiquitous broad-spectrum proteinase inhibitor.</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td class="width-40"><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                    <td>α2M traps the proteinases released by granulocytes during inflammation, such as matrix metalloproteinases (MMPs).</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td class="width-40 "><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                    <td>α2M is also involved in the immune defence reactions acting as a protector against toxic effects by an over production of pro-inflammatory cytokines during inflammation. (Inflammageing).</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td class="width-40 "><i class="fa fa-crosshairs"></i></td>
                                    <td>The plasma protease inhibitor α2M is not present in sufficient concentrations to inactivate the high levels of catabolic factors found in the skin. Findings suggest that supplemental α2M provides anti-aging -protection for the beauty of the skin.</td>
                                </tr>

                            </tbody></table>
                            </div>

                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">Another important element in the plasma is Fibrinogen. Its role is the formation of fibrin that binds together platelets and some plasma proteins in a haemostatic plug. Fibrin is fibrous, non-globular protein. It is formed by the action of protease thrombin on soluble fibrinogen which causes it to polymerize. The cross-linked fibrin forms a 3-dimensional mesh that serves as matrix for migrating cells. </p>
                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify fx animated fadeInRight" data-animate="fadeInRight" style="opacity: 1; visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0ms;">iARF® is an injectable Autologous Regenerative Fibrin produced through ProtSmart 6. That can be used to treat deep lines, creases, folds, and wrinkles, restoring facial volume, and resulting in a more youthful appearance. Injectable Autologous Regenerative Fibrin iARF ® works subtly and gradually over time, providing results that are natural and seamless. iARF ® treatments stimulate your skin’s own natural collagen production to help restore its inner structure and increase the facial volume that has been lost to aging. iARF ® addresses the underlying cause of facial aging, not just the symptoms! The main components are ultra concentrated fibrinogen which binds Plasma proteins with an emphasize on A2M which is anti-inflammatory. Reducing the aging process and platelets which help further repair the cause of aging.6</p>



