                                            <p class="heading-desc t-justify">Injectable platelet-rich fibrin (iPRF) is a liquid form of platelet-rich fibrin (PRF), a natural fibrin matrix derived from the patient''s blood. iPRF contains a high concentration of platelets, growth factors, and cytokines that can potentially promote tissue regeneration, healing, and repair. Unlike PRP, which is platelet-rich plasma, PRF includes a fibrin matrix that allows for a slow and sustained release of growth factors over time, potentially providing longer-lasting therapeutic effects. The injectable form, iPRF, is a more fluid version of PRF, making it suitable for injection into various tissues</p>


