-4Neuroblasts of peripheral neuroblastic tumors are derived from the sympathoadrenal lineage, a division of the ANS. PHOX2B has been observed in peripheral neuroblastic tumors, neuroblastomas, paragangliomas, ganglioneuroblastomas, ganglioneuromas and pheochromocytomas.3,5PHOX2B has been reported to be negative in other small round blue cell tumors.3</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3497/PHOX2B_EP312" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','PHOX2B (EP312) on neuroblastoma.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3497/PHOX2B_EP312','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_422R-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-3497-phox2b-ep312-A45B230A',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/3497/PHOX2B_EP312');
