PAX-8 molecule. This section of the protein is shared with other PAX proteins such as PAX-5 and PAX-6; and thus, some cross-reactivity with these proteins may be observed as evidenced by labeling of selected lymphocytes, and neuroendocrine cells.7</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2127/PAX-8_MRQ-50" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','PAX-8 antibody labels the tumor nuclei in clear cell renal cell carcinoma.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2127/PAX-8_MRQ-50','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_363M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2127-pax-8-mrq-50-E65D4F1A',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2127/PAX-8_MRQ-50');
