land as well as basal epithelium of the respiratory system.1,2NGFR has been shown to be a reliable adjunct marker for melanoma, specifically desmoplastic and spindle cell variants.3-4Anti-NGFR labels myoepithelial cells of the breast and may aid in the differentiation between benign conditions, pre-invasive neoplastic lesions and invasive malignacies of the breast.</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2008/Nerve-Growth-Factor-Receptor-NGFR_MRQ-21" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Anti-NGFR stains myoepithelial cells in sclerosing adenosis of breast.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2008/Nerve-Growth-Factor-Receptor-NGFR_MRQ-21','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_304M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2008-nerve-growth-factor-receptor-ngf-CF89C2C2',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2008/Nerve-Growth-Factor-Receptor-NGFR_MRQ-21');
