radation by enzymes, secretory IgA can survive in harsh environments such as the digestive and respiratory tracts, to provide protection against microbes that multiply in body secretions. It is useful when identifying multiple myeloma.1-3 Note:This product is in obsolescence.IgA (EP170)is available as an alternative.</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/101/IgA_polyclonal" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','IgA (polyclonal) on tonsil.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/101/IgA_polyclonal','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_267A-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-101-iga-polyclonal-96D4B0AC',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/101/IgA_polyclonal');
