<p class="heading-desc t-justify">Mouse CD8 + T Cell Isolation Kit is designed to isolate CD8 + T cells from single-cell suspensions of mouse spleen, lymph nodes, and other tissues by the negative selection method. The principle is to use biotin-labeled monoclonal antibodies to label non-target cells, and then use streptavidin magnetic beads to remove non-target cells, thereby to achieve the purpose of mouse CD8 + T cell sorting. This product can obtain the target cells in only 16 min with the purity rate of up to 96%. There is no abnormal activation of cells after sorting, thus not affecting downstream experiments. The isolation process requires the use of magnetic poles or magnetic racks.</p>

