cinomas.8</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/65/Cytokeratin-8-amp-18_B22-1-amp-B23-1" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Ducts and acini of the salivary gland are labelled by anti-cytokeratin 8 & 18 in a cytoplasmic reaction.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/65/Cytokeratin-8-amp-18_B22-1-amp-B23-1','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_818M-9-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-65-cytokeratin-8-amp-18-b22-1-amp-b23-066238DD',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/65/Cytokeratin-8-amp-18_B22-1-amp-B23-1');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7759','PD-1',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>EP239</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>CM + RabMAb</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology • Hematopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>cytoplasmic, membranous</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>lymph node, tonsil</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Programmed death-1 (PD-1) is expressed on activated T-cells, B-cells, and myeloid cells. Anti-PD-1 is a marker of angioimmunoblastic lymphoma and suggests a unique cell of origin for this neoplasm. Unlike CD10 and BCL6, PD-1 is expressed by few B-cells, so anti-PD-1 may be a more specific and useful marker in the identification of angioimmunoblastic lymphoma. In addition, PD-1 expression provides evidence that angioimmunoblastic lymphoma is a neoplasm derived from germinal center-associated T-cells. PD-1 expression in angioimmunoblastic lymphoma lends further support to this model of T-cell oncogenesis, in which specific subtypes of T-cells may undergo neoplastic transformation and result in specific distinct histologic, immunophenotypic, and clinical subtypes of T-cell neoplasia.1-6 Note:This product is in obsolescence.PD-1 (NAT105)is available as an alternative.</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3562/PD-1_EP239" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','PD-1 (EP239) on Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3562/PD-1_EP239','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_315R-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-3562-pd-1-ep239-F166A2E0',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/3562/PD-1_EP239');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7761','CD35',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>EP197</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>CM + RabMAb</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology • Hematopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Tonsil (Membranous)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:25-1:100*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">CD35, complement receptor 1, is a cell membrane-bound, monomeric glycoprotein on numerous cell types including erythrocytes, leukocytes, glomerular podocytes, and follicular dendritic cells. The primary function of CD35 is to serve as the cellular receptor for C3b and C4b, the most important components of the complement system leading to clearance of foreign macromolecules. The Knops blood group system is a system of antigens located on this protein. The protein mediates cellular binding to particles and immune complexes that have activated complement. Follicular dendritic cells (FDC) are restricted to the B-cell regions of secondary lymphoid follicles. CD35 antigen is found on erythrocytes, B cells, a subset of T cells, monocytes, as well as eosinophils, and neutrophils. Anti-CD35 is considered a mature B-cell marker which labels follicular dendritic reticulum cells and tumors derived from such cells such as follicular dendritic cell tumor/sarcoma.1-6</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3565/CD35_EP197" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','CD35 (EP197) on follicular dendritic cell sarcoma','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3565/CD35_EP197','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_135R-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-3565-cd35-ep197-C0508926',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/3565/CD35_EP197');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7741','STAT6',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>EP325</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>CM + RabMAb</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Soft Tissue Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>nuclear</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>solitary fibrous tumor</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:25-1:100*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">STAT6, a member of the signal transducers and activators of transcription (STAT) family, has been found to form recurrent fusions with NAB2 on chromosome 12q13 in the majority of solitary fibrous tumors.1-3Inactivated STAT6 can be found in the form of a dimer located in the cytoplasm.1STAT6 and NAB2 fusion enables cytosolic STAT6 to migrate to the nucleus and thus allowing for detection in immunohistochemical assays.1NAB2-STAT6 fusion transcriptions have been reported in the majority of solitary fibrous tumors but not in meningiomas, hemangioblastomas, schwannomas, and hemangiomas.1-3This makes STAT6 a useful marker in distinguishing solitary fibrous tumors from other morphologically similar tumors.</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3493/STAT6_EP325" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','STAT6 (EP325) on solitary fibrous tumor.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3493/STAT6_EP325','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_426R-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-3493-stat6-ep325-609B2D8A',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/3493/STAT6_EP325');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7742','MUM1',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>EP190</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>CM + RabMAb</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Hematopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Tonsil (Nuclear); Plasma cell myeloma (Nuclear)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Anti-MUM1 antibody labels a 50kDa, multiple myeloma oncogene-1 (MUM1) protein. MUM1 is encoded by the MUM1/IRF-4 gene, which is mapped to 6q23-25 and identified as a myeloma-associated oncogene.1,2It is a member of the interferon regulatory factor family of transcription factors and plays an important role in the regulation of gene expression in response to signaling by interferon and other cytokines. MUM1 positive cells express the protein in the nucleus in a diffuse and microgranular pattern. However, some positivity is also observed in the cytoplasm of MUM1-expressing cells. In normal/reactive lymphoid tissues, such as lymph node, this antibody stains plasma cells, some B-cells in the light zone of germinal centers, and a subset of T-cells (T-cells in germinal centers and interfollicular areas).1,3MUM1 expression has been described in diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (DLBCL).4-5Anti-MUM1 antibody can stain other B-cell lymphomas such as lymphoplasmacytic lymphoma, chronic lymphocytic leukemia, follicular lymphoma, marginal zone lymphoma, lymphoblastic lymphoma/leukemia, primary effusion lymphoma, DLBCL, Burkitt-like lymphoma, and classical Hodgkin lymphoma.5-7However, the tumor cells in nodular lymphocyte predominant Hodgkin lymphoma are negative or only weakly positive.8MUM1 is also expressed in plasma cell myeloma.9</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3496/MUM1_EP190" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','MUM1 (EP190) on diffuse large B-cell lymphoma.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/3496/MUM1_EP190','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_358R-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-3496-mum1-ep190-026610FC',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/3496/MUM1_EP190');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7604','GLUT1',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>Polyclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Polyclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Cytopathology • Pulmonary Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Colorectal carcinoma (Membranous); Mesothelioma (Membranous)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:50-1:200*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Glucose transporter type I (GLUT1), a prototype member of the GLUT superfamily, is a membrane-associated, erythrocyte glucose transport protein. It is a major glucose transporter in the mammalian blood-brain barrier, and also mediates glucose transport in endothelial cells of the vasculature, adipose tissue, and cardiac muscle. GLUT1 is detectable in many human tissues including those of colon, lung, stomach, and breast. GLUT1 is overexpressed in malignant cells and in a variety of tumors that include mesothelioma and colon carcinoma. Immunohistochemical detection of GLUT1 has been shown to be absent in reactive mesothelium but present in malignant mesothelioma.1,2Anti-GLUT1 is also useful in distinguishing benign endometrial hyperplasia from atypical endometrial hyperplasia and adenocarcinoma.</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2056/GLUT1_Polyclonal" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','GLUT1 is strongly expressed in the cytoplasm and membrane of colorectal carcinoma cells.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2056/GLUT1_Polyclonal','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_355A-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2056-glut1-polyclonal-96291248',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2056/GLUT1_Polyclonal');
