 Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','KBA.62 on skin.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2082/KBA-62_KBA-62','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_366M-9-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2082-kba-62-kba-62-D69257A6',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2082/KBA-62_KBA-62');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7620','Synaptophysin',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>MRQ-40</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Pancreatic islet cells (Cytoplasmic)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Anti-synaptophysin reacts with neuroendocrine cells of human adrenal medulla, pituitary, thyroid, lung, pancreas, and gastrointestinal mucosa. Positive staining is seen in neurons of the brain. This antibody identifies normal neuroendocrine cells and neuroendocrine neoplasms.1-5Diffuse, finely granular, cytoplasmic staining is observed, which probably correlates with the distribution of the antigen within neurosecretory vesicles. Anti-synaptophysin is an independent, broad-range marker of neural and neuroendocrine differentiation.1-9</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2084/Synaptophysin_MRQ-40" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Pancreatic islet cells are labelled in the cytoplasm by anti-synaptophysin.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2084/Synaptophysin_MRQ-40','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_336R-9-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2084-synaptophysin-mrq-40-C90A4D27',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2084/Synaptophysin_MRQ-40');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7814','Cyclin D1',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>SP4</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Hematopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Mantle Cell Lymphoma (Nuclear)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Detection of Cyclin D1 expression by immunohistochemistry (IHC) with Cyclin D1 (SP4) Rabbit Monoclonal Antibody may be used to aid in the diagnosis of mantle cell lymphomas. Cyclin D1 is a nuclear protein that is involved in regulation of the cell cycle.1Cyclin D1 is normally expressed in the G1 (resting) phase of the cell cycle. In normal tissues, cyclin D1 expression by immunohistochemistry is restricted to epithelial tissues, endothelium and some fibroblasts and is not detectable in benign lymphocytes.2Mutations in the cyclin D1 gene can lead to overexpression of cyclin D1 in lymphocytes and deregulation of the normal cell cycle, resulting in malignant transformation. Mantle cell lymphomas typically harbor a t(11;14) (q13;q32) translocation that juxtaposes the CCND1 (cyclin D1) gene with an enhancer of the IgH gene, resulting in cyclin D1 overexpression. Immunohistochemistry for cyclin D1 is positive in mantle cell lymphomas.1-3Immunohistochemistry for cyclin D1 shows a nuclear pattern of staining.</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/63/Cyclin-D1_SP4" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Cyclin D1 (SP4) on lymph node.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/63/Cyclin-D1_SP4','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_241R-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-63-cyclin-d1-sp4-42466F15',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/63/Cyclin-D1_SP4');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7815','Cytokeratin 5 & 6',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>D5 & 16B4</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>cytoplasmic</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>mesothelioma</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:50-1:200*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Twenty identified cytokeratins make up a complex family of intermediate filaments.1Cytokeratin 5 (58kDa) & cytokeratin 6 (56kDa) are type II high molecular weight keratins that are expressed in a broad range of normal tissues including breast, prostate, mesothelium, skin and esophagus.1-3Anti-Cytokeratin 5 & 6 is a useful immunohistochemical marker in the identification of mesothelioma and lung squamous cell carcinoma.1</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/64/Cytokeratin-5-amp-6_D5-16B4" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Cytokeratin 5 & 6 antibody labels mesothelioma cells in a cytoplasmic pattern.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/64/Cytokeratin-5-amp-6_D5-16B4','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_356M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-64-cytokeratin-5-amp-6-d5-16b4-72859AE2',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/64/Cytokeratin-5-amp-6_D5-16B4');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7820','Cytokeratin Cocktail',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>AE1 & AE3</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Breast (Cytoplasmic); Lung (Cytoplasmic); Colon (Cytoplasmic); Skin (Cytoplasmic)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Anti-cytokeratin cocktail (AE1 & AE3) is a broad-spectrum keratin antibody cocktail.1-3It is composed of mouse monoclonal antibody AE1 that recognizes acidic type I keratins 10, 14, 15, 16, 19, and AE3 that reacts with basic type II keratins 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, and 8. Both clones were generated using epidermal keratin as immunogen.1-3This antibody is useful for identifying cells of epithelial origin and detects most carcinomas of different primary sites.1,2This antibody cocktail can cross-react with other intermediate filaments, such as glial fibrillary acidic protein, giving a false-positive staining in glial tumors.4</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/69/Cytokeratin-Cocktail_AE1-amp-AE3" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Cytokeratin Cocktail (AE1 & AE3) on colon.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/69/Cytokeratin-Cocktail_AE1-amp-AE3','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_313M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-69-cytokeratin-cocktail-ae1-amp-ae3-4E85ACD1',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/69/Cytokeratin-Cocktail_AE1-amp-AE3');
