s://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/137/Renal-Cell-Carcinoma_PN-15" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Renal cell carcinoma tumor cells are labelled in a cytoplasmic pattern by anti-renal cell carcinoma.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/137/Renal-Cell-Carcinoma_PN-15','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_329M-9-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-137-renal-cell-carcinoma-pn-15-0BAEF625',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/137/Renal-Cell-Carcinoma_PN-15');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7653','CD33',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>PWS44</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Hematopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>membranous</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>acute myeloid leukemia with monocytic differentiation or with minimal differentiation, placenta syncytiotrophoblasts</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:20-1:80*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">CD33, also known as gp67 or SIGLEC-3, is a 67 kDa glycosylated transmembrane protein that is a member of the sialic acid-binding immunoglobulin-like lectin (siglec) family.1-3Although the precise physiological function of CD33 is unknown, it may mediate cell to cell adhesion and modulate inflammatory and immune response.1-3In normal tissue, anti-CD33 labels myeloid cells (especially myeloid precursors), liver Kupffer cells, lung alveolar macrophages, and placental syncytiotrophoblasts.2,3In neoplastic tissue, anti-CD33 is useful for the identification of acute myeloid leukemia.2,3</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2135/CD33_PWS44" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','CD33 mouse monoclonal antibody stains acute myelomonocytic leukemia strongly in a cytoplasmic pattern.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2135/CD33_PWS44','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_133M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2135-cd33-pws44-C4B9DA6E',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2135/CD33_PWS44');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7654','NSE',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>MRQ-55</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Anatomic Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Pancreas (Cytoplasmic); Carcinoid tumor (Cytoplasmic)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:50-1:200*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Neuron-specific enolase (NSE) is a glycolytic isoenzyme of the enolase gamma-gamma dimer selectively detected in neurons, peripheral nerves, some neuroendocrine cells and tumors.1-3. NSE immunoreactivity is also observed, to a lesser extent, in smooth muscle tissue.4Anti-NSE is often used to visualize peripheral nerves and for the identification of neuroendocrine differentiation.5</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2136/NSE_MRQ-55" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','NSE antibody expresses pancreatic neuroendocrine tumors in a cytoplasmic pattern.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2136/NSE_MRQ-55','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_306M-2-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2136-nse-mrq-55-D79F3170',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2136/NSE_MRQ-55');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7649','TFE3',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>MRQ-37</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Pediatric Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>nuclear</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>testis, melanoma, Xp11.2 translocation renal cell carcinoma</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:50-1:200*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Transcription factor E3 (TFE3) is a protein expressed in many cell types that are encoded by the TFE3 gene. This gene may be involved in chromosomal translocations that occur in some cancers.Xp11 translocation renal cell carcinomas (RCC) are a recently recognized subset of RCC, characterized by chromosome translocations involving the Xp11.2 break point and resulting in gene fusions involving the TFE3 transcription factor gene that maps to this locus.1Alveolar soft part sarcoma (ASPS) is an uncommon soft tissue sarcoma of uncertain differentiation. The hallmark of ASPS is a chromosomal rearrangement at 17q25 and Xp11.2 engendering an ASPSCR1-TFE3 fusion gene responsible for an aberrant transcription factor presumably enabling pathogenesis.1-5</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2129/TFE3_MRQ-37" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','XpII translocated renal cell carcinoma labelled by TFE3 antibody.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2129/TFE3_MRQ-37','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_354R-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2129-tfe3-mrq-37-EB96B9F8',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2129/TFE3_MRQ-37');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7650','FoxP1',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>SP133</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Hematopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>nuclear</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>tonsil, lymph node</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:100-1:500*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Forkhead box P1 (FOXP1) is a transcription factor normally expressed in many cellular processes and plays an important role in development, specifically in human leukocyte populations.1,2Expression of FOXP1 can be found in neoplastic and non-neoplastic tissues.2Overexpression of FOXP1 has been observed in a subset of diffuse large B-cell lymphoma (DLBCL), and thus FOXP1 immunohistochemistry has been shown to be helpful in the subclassification of DLBCL.2</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2130/FoxP1_SP133" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','FoxP1 (SP133) on lymph node.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2130/FoxP1_SP133','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_350R-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2130-foxp1-sp133-3A207070',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2130/FoxP1_SP133');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7591','FLI-1',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>MRQ-1</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Soft Tissue Pathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>nuclear</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>primitive neuroectodermal tumor</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:25-1:100*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">Friend leukemia integration 1 transcription factor (FLI-1) is a protein encoded by the proto-ocogene FLI-1. The FLI-1 protein is best known for its critical role in the pathogenesis of ES/pPNET. FLI-1 is normally expressed in endothelial cells and in hematopoietic cells, including T-lymphocytes. The immunohistochemical detection of FLI-1 protein has been shown in studies to be valuable in the discrimination of Ewing sarcoma/peripheral primitive neuroectodermal tumor (ES/pPNET) from most of its potential mimics. ES/pPNET is a rare primary tumor of the bone/soft tissue that resembles other undifferentiated tumors.1-3</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2027/FLI-1_MRQ-1" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','FLI-1 (MRQ-1) on soft tissue.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2027/FLI-1_MRQ-1','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_254M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2027-fli-1-mrq-1-4030157F',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2027/FLI-1_MRQ-1');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7593','CD4',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>SP35</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Rabbit</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Hematopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td></td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>Tonsil (Cytoplasmic, Membranous); Lymph Node (Cytoplasmic, Membranous)</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:25-1:100*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">CD4 is a 55-kD glycoprotein expressed on the surface of T-helper/regulatory T-cells, monocytes, macrophages, and some dendritic cells. The majority of peripheral T-cell lymphomas are derived from the T-helper/regulatory cell subset so that most mature T-cell neoplasms are CD4+. Anti-CD4 is used to identify normal T-cells and to aid in the identification of neoplasms of T-cell origin.1-3</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2030/CD4_SP35" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Interfollicular T-lymphocytes are highlighted by CD4 antibody in a cytoplasmic pattern. Note scattered intrafollicular T-cells also express CD4 antigen.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/2030/CD4_SP35','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_104R-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-2030-cd4-sp35-5C0688D4',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/2030/CD4_SP35');
Insert into WEB.PRODUCTS (DELETED,ACTIVE,PRODUCT_ID,PRODUCT_NAME,PRODUCT_NAME_WEB,SHORT_NAME,PRODUCT_SIPPLIER_ORDER,SUPPLIER_ID,DISCIPLINE,PRODUCT_GROUP,PRODUCT_TYPE,CLASS_ID,CLASS_COLOUR,ABOUT_1,ABOUT_2,PRODUCT_LINK,PRODUCT_ENQUIRE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL,PRODUCT_IMAGE_1,PRODUCT_IMAGE_2,PRODUCT_IMAGE_3,PRODUCT_IMAGE_4,PRODUCT_PARENT_ID,DATE_CREATED,DATE_DELETED,ANCHOR_ID,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_LARGE_HEIGHT,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_WIDTH,PRODUCT_IMAGE_SMALL_HEIGHT,SUPPLIER_NAME,DISCIPLINE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_ID,PRODUCT_TYPE_ID,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT,PRODUCT_GROUP_TYPE_ALT_ID,BUSINESS,PRODUCT_IMAGE_EXTERNAL,PROUDUCT_SKU,SUPPLIER_PRODUCT_ID) values ('N','Y','PRD-7526','S-100',null,null,null,'SUP-0003','Histopathology','Antibodies','Reagents',null,null,'<div class="antibody-outer-wrap ">  <div class="antibody-drawer-box">    <div class="antibody-info-table-wrap">      <table class="antibody-info-table">        <tr><th>Clone:</th><td>4C4.9</td></tr>        <tr><th>Brand:</th><td>Cell Marque</td></tr>        <tr><th>Host:</th><td>Mouse</td></tr>        <tr><th>Antibody Type:</th><td>Monoclonal</td></tr>        <tr><th>Specialties:</th><td>Dermatopathology</td></tr>        <tr><th>Visualization:</th><td>cytoplasmic, nuclear</td></tr>        <tr><th>Control:</th><td>melanoma</td></tr>        <tr><th>Dilution Range:</th><td>1:50-1:200*</td></tr>        <tr>          <td colspan="2" class="antibody-details-cell">            <div class="antibody-vis-label"><strong>Details:</strong></div>            <div class="antibody-desc">S-100 protein has been found in normal melanocytes, Langerhans cells, histiocytes, chondrocytes, lipocytes, skeletal and cardiac muscle, Schwann cells, epithelial and myoepithelial cells of the breast, salivary and sweat glands, as well as in glial cells.1,2,6Neoplasms derived from these cells also express S-100 protein, albeit non-uniformly.1-4A large number of well differentiated tumors of the salivary gland, adipose and cartilaginous tissue,3and Schwann cell-derived tumors express S-100 protein. Almost all malignant melanomas and cases of histiocytosis X are positive for S-100 protein.4,5Despite the fact that S-100 protein is an ubiquitous substance, its demonstration is of great value in the identification of several neoplasms, particularly melanomas.1-6</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/138/S-100_4C4-9" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Cytoplasmic labelling by S-100 antibody on melanoma tumor cells.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/138/S-100_4C4-9','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_330M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-138-s-100-4c4-9-C4A39C13',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/138/S-100_4C4-9');
