tumors.3-9 Note:This product is in obsolescence.Inhibin Alpha (MRQ-63)is available as an alternative.</div>          </td>        </tr>      </table>    </div>    <div class="antibody-link-button">      <a href="https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/105/Inhibin-alpha_R1" target="_blank" title="View Cell Marque Product Page">        <img src="#WORKSPACE_FILES#assets/images/Scientific/suppliers/Cell_Marque/cell_marque-logo.png" alt="View Product" class="product-link-image">      </a>    </div>  </div></div>','Granulosa cells in the ovary are strongly highlighted by the inhibin antibody with cytoplasmic staining.','https://www.cellmarque.com/antibodies/CM/105/Inhibin-alpha_R1','#','https://www.cellmarque.com/cmsial-images/TH_271M-1-ihc-01.jpg',null,null,null,null,null,null,to_date('24-APR-26','DD-MON-RR'),null,'_cm-105-inhibin-alpha-r1-56BDAAD0',null,null,null,null,'Cell Marque','DIS-0001','PRG-0001','PTY-0003',null,null,'Syntec Scientific','Y',null,'CM/105/Inhibin-alpha_R1');
